(firstQuint)Aggressive Prostate Cancers in Elderly Patients.

 Patients aged 70 years or older had a higher risk of advanced prostate cancer and shorter BCR-free survival than younger ones.

 Definite treatment of clinically localized prostate cancer should be actively considered in well-selected healthy patients older than 70 years.

